# Shopify credentials for `npm run deploy:shopify`.
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in the values.
#
# The deploy uses the Shopify CLI with a Theme Access token:
#   1. Install the free "Theme Access" app: https://apps.shopify.com/theme-access
#   2. In it, add a user with your email — Shopify emails you a token (shptka_...)
#   3. Paste that token below as SHOPIFY_ADMIN_TOKEN.
#
# Find SHOPIFY_THEME_ID in the theme editor URL:
#   admin.shopify.com/store/<store>/themes/<THEME_ID>/editor

SHOPIFY_STORE=y4i4ta-hn.myshopify.com
SHOPIFY_ADMIN_TOKEN=shptka_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
SHOPIFY_THEME_ID=202232136025

# ── Catalogue admin app (npm run admin) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Optional Admin API credentials that let the admin app create products (with
# per-size variants + stock) automatically. The Theme Access token above only
# works for theme assets, NOT the Admin API. Without these the admin app
# still pushes sprites and writes an import-ready CSV instead.
#
# Apps created in the Dev Dashboard (the only option since Jan 2026) no longer
# show a static Admin API token — they give a Client ID + Client Secret, which
# the admin server exchanges for a 24h access token automatically (OAuth
# client credentials grant, auto-refreshed):
#   1. https://dev.shopify.com → create an app for your store
#   2. Configure Admin API access scopes: write_products, write_inventory,
#      read_locations, write_publications
#   3. Install the app on the store
#   4. App → Settings → copy the Client ID and Client Secret:
# SHOPIFY_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# SHOPIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Legacy alternative: a static Admin API token (shpat_...) from a custom app
# created in the Shopify admin before the Dev Dashboard migration. Takes
# precedence over the client credentials when both are set:
# SHOPIFY_PRODUCTS_TOKEN=shpat_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Optional overrides for the admin app:
# SHOPIFY_API_VERSION=2026-01
# ADMIN_PORT=5190
# ADMIN_DRY_RUN=1   # test the flow without touching Shopify
